ata\";s:131:\"With the latest update from WordPress.com\'s JetPack, installing email subscriptions on your blog is so easy that anybody can do it!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Christopher Ross\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2867:\"<p>This week has been a banner release week for the team at <strong>WordPress.com</strong>, first they added <a title=\"WordPress.com adds Drag and Drop file uploads\" href=\"http://thisismyurl.com/6833/wordpresscom-adds-drag-drop-file-uploads/\">drag and drop file uploads to WordPress.com</a> and now today I updated <strong><a href=\"http://jetpack.me\">JetPack</a></strong> (a free plugin by WordPress.com) to find they&#8217;d added some powerful, cool new features to the <strong>WordPress.org</strong> tool.</p>\n<h2>Add easy email subscriptions to your WordPress blog</h2>\n<p><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-6843\" src=\"http://thisismyurl.rodonic.com/files/2011/11/JetPack-Subscriptions.png\" alt=\"JetPack Subscriptions Email Subscriptions have come to WordPress blogs\" width=\"239\" height=\"225\" title=\"Email Subscriptions have come to WordPress blogs\" />What caught my attention as soon as the update was complete was the new email subscription widget which will allow users to be updated via email when posts and comments change on my website.</p>\n<p><strong>Permission based marketing</strong> such as email subscriptions to your blog are a core indicator of how well your website is doing because unlike click throughs and sales, email subscriptions are from people who have chosen to have you market to them. Much like <strong>Facebook</strong> fans and <strong>Twitter</strong> followers, these are the committed members of your community who are most likely to share and repost your blog articles.</p>\n<h2>How do you add email subscriptions to your WordPress blog?</h2>\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t already done so, open up your WordPress administration panel (located at yourdomain<em>/wp-admin/</em>) and click on <em>Plugins</em> &gt; <em>Add New</em>. Search for and install JetPack, once activated you&#8217;re ready to go to the next step.</p>\n<p>Next, navigate to <em>Appearance</em> &gt; <em>Widgets</em> and look for <strong>Blog Subscriptions (JetPack)</strong>. Once you&#8217;ve found it, simply drag it to the appropriate sidebar on the right hand side of the screen and set it up. You&#8217;re all done!</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-6844\" src=\"http://thisismyurl.rodonic.com/files/2011/11/Install-Email-Subscription-on-WordPress.jpg\" alt=\"Install Email Subscription on WordPress Email Subscriptions have come to WordPress blogs\" width=\"650\" height=\"329\" title=\"Email Subscriptions have come to WordPress blogs\" /></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/32BAXw5OA03ANVV2PtfMTQ8gutI/0/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/32BAXw5OA03ANVV2PtfMTQ8gutI/0/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/32BAXw5OA03ANVV2PtfMTQ8gutI/1/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/32BAXw5OA03ANVV2PtfMTQ8gutI/1/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/11/18/email-subscriptions-wordpress-blogs/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"WordPress.com adds Drag and Drop file uploads\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/11/17/wordpresscom-adds-drag-drop-file-uploads/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/11/17/wordpresscom-adds-drag-drop-file-uploads/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 17 Nov 2011 17:43:23 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"http://thisismyurl.com/?p=6833\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"Did Chris-e-mas come early for me or is WordPress just getting more amazing everyday?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Christopher Ross\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2245:\"<p>This morning I woke up to find the elves at <strong>WordPress</strong> command have added two new and brutally cool features to <strong>WordPress.com</strong>, we can assume these are part of the upcoming <strong>WordPress.org</strong> self-hosted download as well.</p>\n<h2>Drag and Drop File Uploads in WordPress</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://thisismyurl.rodonic.com/files/2011/11/WordPress-Drag-and-Drop.png\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-6834\" src=\"http://thisismyurl.rodonic.com/files/2011/11/WordPress-Drag-and-Drop-300x98.png\" alt=\"WordPress Drag and Drop 300x98 WordPress.com adds Drag and Drop file uploads\" width=\"300\" height=\"98\" title=\"WordPress.com adds Drag and Drop file uploads\" /></a>How cool it this? When you want to upload a file to <a title=\"WordPress consulting and marketing\" href=\"http://thisismyurl.com\">WordPress</a>, the old school dialog for selecting and uploading a file but now there&#8217;s a simple drag and drop interface for moving files straight from your computer to WordPress.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s as easy as copying a file from one folder to the other.</p>\n<h2>New Fly Out Menus in WordPress.com</h2>\n<p>Improving the WordPress interface is an ongoing process and the new updates to the menu system are sure to have critics as well as supporters, I fall firmly under the support column for this new menu change, it moves the menus to the right of titles instead of appearing under the main heading.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-6835\" src=\"http://thisismyurl.rodonic.com/files/2011/11/WordPress-Fly-Out-Menus.png\" alt=\"WordPress Fly Out Menus WordPress.com adds Drag and Drop file uploads\" width=\"650\" height=\"214\" title=\"WordPress.com adds Drag and Drop file uploads\" /></p>\n<p>WordPress 3.3 is scheduled for release in about a month, what do you think of the new changes?</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/J7XYsMxW2D3xEzSK2Hv74PvT5C8/0/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/J7XYsMxW2D3xEzSK2Hv74PvT5C8/0/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/J7XYsMxW2D3xEzSK2Hv74PvT5C8/1/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/J7XYsMxW2D3xEzSK2Hv74PvT5C8/1/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/11/17/wordpresscom-adds-drag-drop-file-uploads/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"6\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"Make a Living with WordPress, Detroit Style\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/11/16/make-a-living-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/11/16/make-a-living-wordpress/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 16 Nov 2011 03:15:16 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Blog\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Bloggers\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Detroit\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"WordCamp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"http://thisismyurl.com/?p=6822\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"I thought I was in love with WordPress until I met the love of my life, and her escort.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Christopher Ross\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5276:\"<p><img class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-6823\" src=\"http://thisismyurl.rodonic.com/files/2011/11/WordCamp-Detroit-Why-You-So-Good.jpg\" alt=\"WordCamp Detroit Why You So Good Make a Living with WordPress, Detroit Style\" width=\"301\" height=\"301\" title=\"Make a Living with WordPress, Detroit Style\" />Oh <strong><a title=\"WordCamp\" href=\"http://wordcamp.org\">WordCamp</a></strong>, why did you have to end? I was having so much fun with you.</p>\n<p>Luckily however, my blog is here to remind you of all the great things we talked about and push you to the epic win!</p>\n<p>What exactly did we talk about? Before we even got started with the real subject, I told all of you a few things that I consider important.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>I am the child of mean parents who didn&#8217;t let me have video games, this forced me to <strong>learn to program</strong> at an early age (we&#8217;ll talk about the cookie cupboard another time);</li>\n<li>This weekend I <strong>fell in love</strong>, even though she didn&#8217;t take me up on my offer for a weekend of fun in Motor city and came with her own security guard. I am now on Team Corvette;</li>\n<li><strong>Free is not a business model</strong>. I&#8217;ll come clean and admit that I stole that from <a href=\"http://howardlindzon.com/\">Howard Lindzon</a>, he&#8217;s awesome and full of great pieces of advice;</li>\n<li>We <strong>talked about sex</strong> and how to have fun while working with WordPress, the world&#8217;s coolest blogging platform. We also talked about money and power but I noticed a few heads perk up at the first part of that subject;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>More to the point, I told you that <strong>WordPress</strong>is remarkable and that if you really want to put in the effort, building a phenomenal lifestyle with WordPress was more than possible &#8230; it&#8217;s actually pretty easy as long as you&#8217;re willing to work for it.</p>\n<h2>You don&#8217;t really want to make money.</h2>\n<p>Money is for suckers, that&#8217;s what we talked about. OK not really but we did talk about the fact that money is only one of the things you can get from working with WordPress. So what do I think you really want?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Indulgence</strong>, with covers everything from sex and great food to travel and fun. It&#8217;s about what you want, even though you might not need it.</li>\n<li><strong>Security</strong> comes from WordPress in the form of money and it&#8217;s all the things you need (mortgage, insurance etc)</li>\n<li><strong>Authority</strong>, which is a word that I like more than both celebrity or power.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you can figure out a way to gain those three things, in which ever balance you want &#8230; you&#8217;re earning a living from WordPress.</p>\n<h2>There are five ways to <a title=\"Make a living with WordPress\" href=\"http://thisismyurl.com/6822/make-a-living-wordpress/\">make a living with WordPress</a></h2>\n<p>In the talk we covered five ways to make a living with WordPress but I know that there are more, these are just the ones that I&#8217;ve figured out, you&#8217;re welcome to share more with me in the comments below.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Be like <a title=\"@bavotasan\" href=\"http://twitter.com/bavotasan\">@bavotasan</a> (<a title=\"Montreal WordPress Developer\" href=\"http://bavotasan.com\">bavotasan.com</a>) and <strong>develop amazing free WordPress themes</strong> and plugins for the WordPress community and offer upgrades, premium services and support;</li>\n<li>Help out in the forums and write <strong>WordPress books / tutorials</strong> like <a href=\"http://twitter.com/andrea_r\">@andrea_r</a> (<a title=\"WordPress Multisite Consulting\" href=\"http://ronandandrea.com\">ronandandrea.com</a>);</li>\n<li>Become a <strong>WordPress coder or consultant</strong> like me (<a title=\"WordPress Consulting Canada\" href=\"http://twitter.com/thisismyurl\">@thisismyurl</a>) and <a title=\"WordPress\" href=\"http://twitter.com/billericson\">@billericson</a>, make money helping people have better WordPress websites</li>\n<li>Get a job working for the man. WordPress is huge, tons of companies are looking to <strong>hire WordPress developers</strong> and bloggers;</li>\n<li>Write for <strong>WordPress blogs</strong>. I should have given a shout out to <a href=\"http://wpcandy.com/\">WPCandy</a> who was in the room, they do amazing work and are on the top of my RSS feeds;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Are there more ways to <strong><a title=\"Make a living with WordPress\" href=\"http://thisismyurl.com/6822/make-a-living-wordpress/\">make a living with WordPress</a></strong>? Yes, of course .. but I don&#8217;t know them all. What I do know is that in <strong><a title=\"WordCamp Detroit\" href=\"http://2011.detroit.wordcamp.org\">WordCamp Detroit</a></strong>, the crowd was amazing and if anybody knows how to make a living with WordPress &#8230; I bet you guys do, so why not share?</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/BkgGeHaNPTFYRCewS18hhXgy3HE/0/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/BkgGeHaNPTFYRCewS18hhXgy3HE/0/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/BkgGeHaNPTFYRCewS18hhXgy3HE/1/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/BkgGeHaNPTFYRCewS18hhXgy3HE/1/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://thisismyurl.com/2011/11/16/make-a-living-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5